{
  "stem": "4247.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She gave everything for the family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "However, with retrospect, I realize that she was-- because of-- of the fact that the family occupied all-- all of her heart, she was unable to give-- nothing was left for anybody else.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So certainly, nothing was left-- was nothing left for-- for the neighbor, who happened to be non-Jewish, of course, which wasn't in his favor in any case, in my grandmother's philosophy.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and she didn't have a great deal of time for even her Jewish neighbor, had it been a Jewish neighbor.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the family was all her life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that took all her energy, all her emotional reserves.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was my-- that was my Jewish background coming from there as a small child.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was the only boy in the family as a grandchild.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All the others were girls, so that secured a very strong position for me on the top of that, you see?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and-- and that background was passed onto my mother, who had a kosher household.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not-- not as strict as my grandmother, but it was kosher.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember we-- we had the-- had been taking the chickens to be killed by the religious ritual, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went to shul, we went-- we observed the major-- major-- major Jewish holidays.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, our religious activity was-- was somewhat diluted in comparison to what I've seen at my grandfathers, grandmothers place.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, this religious background, of course, was mixed, as I originally told you, with the Hungarian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] education system, right?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the-- the-- my peers, my school surrounding, were so strong that my younger childhood was completely taken over by it.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
